  "prompt": "What would be the top 10% bay area salary for PhD with 7 years experience, in different technical fields?",
  "response": "Salaries can vary significantly based on the specific technical field, the company, and other factors such as location within the Bay Area, but I can provide you with approximate figures based on trends up to 2023. Here are estimated top 10% salary ranges for PhD holders with around 7 years of experience across various technical fields in the Bay Area:\n\n1. **Computer Science / Software Engineering**: \n   - Top 10%: $180,000 - $220,000+\n\n2. **Data Science / Machine Learning**: \n   - Top 10%: $180,000 - $230,000+\n\n3. **Electrical Engineering**: \n   - Top 10%: $160,000 - $200,000+\n\n4. **Bioinformatics / Computational Biology**: \n   - Top 10%: $150,000 - $190,000+\n\n5. **Chemical Engineering**: \n   - Top 10%: $150,000 - $190,000+\n\n6. **Physics / Applied Physics**: \n   - Top 10%: $150,000 - $200,000+\n\n7. **Mechanical Engineering**: \n   - Top 10%: $140,000 - $180,000+\n\n8. **Economics / Quantitative Finance**: \n   - Top 10%: $180,000 - $250,000+\n\n9. **Mathematics / Statistics**: \n   - Top 10%: $160,000 - $210,000+\n\n10. **Artificial Intelligence / Robotics**: \n    - Top 10%: $190,000 - $250,000+\n\nThese figures reflect base salaries and do not typically include bonuses, stock options, or other forms of compensation that are common in the tech industry. Additionally, the Bay Area's cost of living is notably high, which is often a factor when considering salary levels. Always check current salary data from reliable sources, such as Glassdoor, Payscale, or industry reports, to get the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
